$interpreted: Chiyuki: Savior... How are you? It's been three days since you've left, and I've started a diary.
Chiyuki: I'm not sure why... I guess there are just some things I don't want to forget.
Chiyuki: ...I've asked a lot about the past these past few days. Although, to be honest, I'm just an actress. I don't know about justice, right and wrong...
Chiyuki: But, because of you, a lot of people have been second-guessing the Alliance these past few days. Maybe that's what you wanted...
Upset Citizen: We want answers!! Innocent people got hurt at the finals, why are you remaining silent!!?
Loud Citizen: Yeah! And the Dream Flower got destroyed, so now how are we gonna choose a new arbiter!?
Maeok: You're right, everyone, some horrible things happened at the finals. And yet, as you can see...
Maeok: This belonged to the criminal! He has been apprehended and will be given his just dues!
Surprised Citizen: She's right! That did belong to him!
Happy Citizen: Yay! Arbiter Maeok is a hero! A hero!!
Maeok: Now, about the Dream Flower... It may have been destroyed, but we're sure the Holy Dragon will point us down a new path.
Faithful Citizen: Yeah! The Holy Dragon won't forsake us!
Loud Citizen: But then what about the finals!? Who won!?
Maeok: Ahem... Please, worry not. While there were some hiccups, the Keeper of the Udumbara did select an arbiter, in the end.
Maeok: Behold everyone, the winner of the Martial Arts Tournament and your new arbiter---
Maeok: Tindoiimu!
Loud Citizen: What!? The bug!? How!?!?
Tindoiimu: Well, here's my Udumbara flower. You can see for yourself.
Surprised Citizen: I-It's really a flower from the Udumbara itself!
Upset Citizen: No way! I don't want her!!
Tapir Chieftain: This flower, very old, I attest, it is real. She is, accepted by, Keeper of the Udumbara, and, Holy Dragon.
Angry Citizen: How the hell is a maggot gonna be our new arbiter!? No way!!
Maeok: Quiet! I realize you might not all be excited about this outcome, but it is an outcome you all must respect!
Maeok: It is tradition, and a tradition that holds us together! If we disrespect it, we might as well turn our backs on the Holy Dragon altogether!
Maeok: Now, I hope you all reflect on this and give your blessings to our new arbiter tomorrow at the ceremony.
Qing-Feng: Arbiter Maeok is correct, we must uphold tradition. Let us give our "blessings" to our new arbiter tomorrow.
Maeok: Now, enough of this talk. I should tell you all some news you'll want to hear.
Maeok: Although it's not time for the award ceremony, we do have a new Alliance Beauty!
Maeok: Our new beauty won by a large margin, which is understandable after her display of bravery the other day.
Maeok: That's right, she's not only strikingly beautiful, but also courageous and loyal. Let's put our hands together for our new Alliance Beauty---Chiyuki!!
Happy Citizen: It's Chiyuki! Chiyuki, you're the best!!
Chiyuki: ...Well, we've come to see this day.
Chiyuki: This tournament has definitely been eventful, to say the least. But, we've all come together and let tradition guide us here!
Chiyuki: Maybe because most of you, like me, need something tangible to show you the way.
Wolf Chieftain: Well, if it isn't our Alliance Beauty.
Wolf Chieftain: Shouldn't you be getting ready for the ceremony? What are you doing here alone?
Chiyuki: Um... It's a bit too crowded out there. I thought I'd sit here for a bit and collect my thoughts.
Turtle Chieftain: Yes, you've been quite the busy bee as of late. You should collect your thoughts... collect your thoughts...
Turtle Chieftain: I guess all the effort we put in campaigning for you wasn't in vain.
Chiyuki: ...Oh? Well, thank you for your support...
Wolf Chieftain: No need to thank us, we're all family here~
Wolf Chieftain: And yet, if you wanted to "really" thank us, well... we definitely wouldn't object.
Chiyuki: Ah... I...
Turtle Chieftain: Hyehe... I bet you know what we're talking about, right?
Chiyuki: Chieftain, have some respect!
Turtle Chieftain: Since that "savior" of yours won't be stepping in this time, I think we should have a little fun~
Chiyuki: (No one's coming to save me this time...)
Chiyuki: St-Stop!!
Chiyuki: If you two won't respect me, then I won't respect you!
Turtle Chieftain: Brat, you think you're so much better than us? You'll never learn your lesson, having everyone fawn all over you all the time.
Puggi: The lady said~~~hands off!!
Chiyuki: Puggi!? What are you doing here!?
Hestia: We were coming to congratulate you, but then we saw this...
Wolf Chieftain: Ludicrous! You loudmouthed little bird, how dare you hit me!?
Puggi: Shut up, old man! I don't take kindly to pervs like you!
Puggi: Leave it to me, ladies! The Main Character is about turn these pigs into bacon!
Turtle Chieftain: Hmph, I won't forget this!!
Puggi: Hmph, chumps like that... can't even call 'em a miniboss.
Chiyuki: Thank you so much... Whew, I feel much better now.
Puggi: Don't mention it, it's my job as the Main Character to help damsels in distress. Too bad Pang wasn't here, or I woulda kicked those scrubs into next week.
Chiyuki: Help... Just like, back then, he helped me...
Puggi: ...I don't know what you're talking about, but you don't seem too jazzed about it.
Chiyuki: Oh? Can you hear that in my voice?
Puggi: Of course. As the Main Character, it's important to be a hyper-sensitive listener, to read between the lines!
Puggi: Believe me, I've got a lot of pain behind these eyes. Pain that makes me the man I am today.
Puggi: Some of those painful experiences led me to Pang, too. I'm thankful for all of them.
Hestia: Sorry, sometimes Puggi doesn't make any sense. Actually, most of the time...
Chiyuki: That's quite alright... I actually think I kind of understand him, hehe...
Puggi: Finally, that sweet smile once again!
Chiyuki: I thought I'm always smiling?
Puggi: Hmm... Perhaps, but, it's been different lately.
Chiyuki: ...Maybe you're the only one who can really see the difference, Puggi. You and... him.
Hestia: Him...? Who are you talking about, Chiyuki? The guy you said saved you?
Chiyuki: Oh, nothing. Like what Puggi said, he's just another experience... one who made me into who I am today.
Chiyuki: Puggi... Thank you.
Chiyuki: If you don't mind, I actually have a request.
Chiyuki: Would you two come with me to the ceremony?
Puggi: Of course, I belong in the spotlight!
Chiyuki: (My savior... I will not stand by and be a victim any longer. I will fight for the respect of others, fight for my right...)
Tindoiimu: (Tomorrow... I'll finally be the arbiter, tomorrow.)
Tindoiimu: (After that, everything that's happened to my people... all that torture will finally come to an end.)
Soohyeon: You're a good person, I know you are... Why become just like them?
Tindoiimu: (I'm not like them at all.)
Tindoiimu: (Petals...?)
Tindoiimu: (Come to think of it, I saw these back then...)
Tindoiimu: (...Back then... Somewhere I can never go back to. I can only move forward, now.)
Tindoiimu: ……
Juan-Yun: Nervous about tomorrow?
Juan-Yun: Enjoying the evening, Princess? I'm here uninvited once again~
Juan-Yun: Why aren't you speaking? Why are you looking at me like that? I'm not used to it...
Tindoiimu: ...I heard you were hurt. Is it serious?
Juan-Yun: Nothing serious, thanks to Maeok.
Juan-Yun: It's rare to hear you asking how I am. Maybe you've softened a bit, now that you're becoming arbiter?
Tindoiimu: I'm not in the mood for jokes.
Juan-Yun: Sorry, I just didn't want to scare your guest. Just trying to lighten the mood.
Tindoiimu: My guest?
Tindoiimu: Tingko!?
TIngko: Princess!
Tindoiimu: What are you doing here!? D-Did something happen to the tribe!?
TIngko: No, everyone's fine! I just came to congratulate you, and give you some news.
Tindoiimu: News?
Tingko: Jihasaha and all them were so happy to hear that you won, that you're becoming arbiter.
TIngko: It gave them a huge burst of morale, they've been killing so many Alliance soldiers, gaining back so much of our lost land!
Juan-Yun: Ah... To me, that sounds a bit inauspicious, and yet... I understand that Tindoiimu becoming arbiter must give motivation to so many.
Tingko: I wanted to tell you this news myself, so I had Juan-Yun sneak me in here.
Tindoiimu: You shouldn't have snuck in here like that, it's too dangerous! I'm not arbiter yet, what if something happened to you!?
TIngko: I know, I'm sorry... But then I thought of you fighting on your own for all this time, and I...
Tindoiimu: I'm sorry for worrying all of you... It must have been hard coming all this way.
TIngko: Nope, it was fine~ Just knowing I'd see you again made the trek easier!
Tindoiimu: I supposed I haven't thanked you yet, Juan-Yun.
Juan-Yun: That's right! I was starting to feel invisible over here!
Tindoiimu: Well... I'm sorry.
Juan-Yun: Well, I suppose you two have much to talk about. I've bribed the guards, so they won't bother you. And neither will I.
Tindoiimu: Wait.
Tindoiimu: I know you put yourself in danger by bringing Tingko in here.
Tindoiimu: So... Thank you, really.
Juan-Yun: What a dangerous smile~ If it brought you happiness, then it is my pleasure.
Tindoiimu: Still hasn't changed a bit...
Tingko: Princess~?
Tindoiimu: By the way... Jihasaha had no qualms about you coming here?
TIngko: He did, but I was adamant about coming. In the end, he couldn't do anything to stop me.
Tindoiimu: Well, it seems like you two have gotten closer, then. It's good to hear that.
Tingko: Well, I wouldn't say "close", even though he definitely is taking good care of me...
Tindoiimu: Don't overthink it.
Tingko: You know, Jihasaha's been really worried about you, Princess.
TIngko: Oh yeah, I almost forgot! Juan-Yun just told me that the Alliance got something really cool for the ceremony tomorrow!
TIngko: They booked a traveling circus troupe!
Tindoiimu: Traveling circus...?
TIngko: And, I heard that troupe is called...
Yonghyeon: Tindoiimu! Get out here right now!!
